# :menuselection:`Armature --> Transform --> Scale Radius`
msgid ":menuselection:`Armature --> Transform --> Scale Radius`"
msgstr ":menuselection:`Cốt (Armature) --> Biến Hóa (Transform) --> Đổi Tỷ Lệ Bán Kính (Scale Radius)`"

msgid "Hotkey"
msgstr "Phím Tắt"

msgid ":kbd:`Alt-S`"
msgstr ":kbd:`:kbd:`Alt-S``"

msgid "You can alter the radius that a bone has by selecting the head, body or tail of a bone, and then press :kbd:`Alt-S` and move the mouse left or right. If the body is selected the mean radius will be scaled. And as usual, with connected bones, you scale at the same time the radius of the parent's tip and of the children's roots."
msgstr "You can alter the radius that a bone has by selecting the head, body or tail of a bone, and then press :kbd:`:kbd:`Alt-S`` and move the mouse left or right. If the body is selected the mean radius will be scaled. And as usual, with connected bones, you scale at the same time the radius of the parent's tip and of the children's roots."

# You can also alter the bone radius by selecting the tail or head of the bone you wish to alter, then navigate to :menuselection:`Properties Editor --> Bone --> Deform --> Radius Section` and entering new values for the *Đuôi -- Tail* and *Đầu -- Head* number fields.
msgid "You can also alter the bone radius by selecting the tail or head of the bone you wish to alter, then navigate to :menuselection:`Properties Editor --> Bone --> Deform --> Radius Section` and entering new values for the *Tail* and *Head* number fields."
msgstr "You can also alter the bone radius by selecting the tail or head of the bone you wish to alter, then navigate to :menuselection:`Trình Biên Soạn Tính Chất (Properties Editor) --> Xương (Bone) --> Biến Dạng (Deform) --> Phần Bán Kính (Radius Section)` and entering new values for the *Tail* and *Head* number buttons."

msgid "Bone Scale and Scale Radius comparison."
msgstr "Bone Scale and Scale Radius comparison."

msgid "A single selected bone in Octahedron visualization."
msgstr "A single selected bone in Octahedron visualization."

msgid "After normal scale."
msgstr "After normal scale."

msgid "A single selected bone in Envelope visualization."
msgstr "A single selected bone in Envelope visualization."

msgid "After Scaled Radius. Its length remains the same, but its joints' radius are bigger."
msgstr "After Scaled Radius. Its length remains the same, but its joints' radius are bigger."

msgid "Note that, when you resize a bone (either by directly scaling it, or by moving one of its joints), Blender automatically adjusts the end-radii of its envelope proportionally to the size of the modification. Therefore, it is advisable to place all the bones first, and only then edit their properties."
msgstr "Note that, when you resize a bone (either by directly scaling it, or by moving one of its joints), Blender automatically adjusts the end-radii of its envelope proportionally to the size of the modification. Therefore, it is advisable to place all the bones first, and only then edit their properties."

