msgstr "This tool is not available from the *Armature* menu, but only from the *Specials* pop-up menu :kbd:`W`. It allows you to switch the direction of the selected bones (i.e. their root will become their tip, and vice versa)."

msgid "Switching the direction of a bone will generally break the chain(s) it belongs to. However, if you switch a whole (part of a) chain, the switched bones will still be parented/connected, but in \"reversed order\". See the Fig. :ref:`fig-rig-properties-switch`."
msgstr "Switching the direction of a bone will generally break the chain(s) it belongs to. However, if you switch a whole (part of a) chain, the switched bones will still be parented/connected, but in \"reversed order\". See the Fig. :ref:`fig-rig-properties-switch`."

